[normal]Each of our 39 County Cricket Boards now 
[normal]has a
[normal] 
[normal]performance pathway in place that provide
[normal]s
[normal] opportunities for girls and women to compete in county cricket.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In 2012 t
[normal]he ECB also introduced a new women’s club competition structure in which the pinnacle of club cricket was expanded to increase the number of top level clubs, and other leagues link to the linear structure. Counties are now investing in running and developi
[normal]ng their own junior and senior leagues to meet demand. Leagues are run throughout the week or at weekends
[normal].  
